;BIOMOLECULE: 1, 2, 3, 4
THIS ENTRY CONTAINS THE CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC ASYMMETRIC 
UNIT WHICH CONSISTS OF 4 CHAIN(S). SEE REMARK 350 
FOR INFORMATION ON GENERATING THE BIOLOGICAL 
MOLECULE(S).
Complex A consists of chains B and C;
Complex B consists of chains A and D;
Complex A' consists of chains F and G;
Complex B' consists of chains E and H.
;
999 
;SEQUENCE
According to the authors, this apparent conflict is 
due to the use of HIV-1 strain NL4-3 which
has a histidine at residue 120.
;
